{{Infobox scientist | name = Jean-Pierre Jouannaud | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Jean Pierre Jouannaud.jpg | imagesize = | alt = | caption = May 2008 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1947|05|21|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Aix-les-Bains]] | death_date = <!--{{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1947|05|21|df=y}} --> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = [[Paris]] | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = | workplaces = | patrons = | alma_mater = | thesis1_title = Filtres digitaux autoadaptifs: algorithmes de calcul et simulation | thesis1_url = | thesis1_year = 1972 | thesis2_title = Sur l'inférence et la synthèse automatiques de fonctions LISP à partir d'exemples | thesis2_url = | thesis2_year = 1977 | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = [[CNRS Silver Medal]] 1986, [[Prix Michel Montpetit]] 2000 | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{URL|http://www.lix.polytechnique.fr/Labo/Jean-Pierre.Jouannaud}} | footnotes = }}
'''Jean-Pierre Jouannaud''' is a French computer scientist, known for his work in the area of [[term rewriting]].
He was born on 21 May 1947 in [[Aix-les-Bains]] (France). From 1967 to 1969 he visited the [[Ecole Polytechnique]] (Paris). In 1970, 1972, and 1977, he wrote his Master thesis ([[Master of Advanced Studies#Master of advanced studies (MAS) as diplôme d'études approfondies (DEA) in France and francophone countries|DEA]]), [[PhD thesis]] (Thèse de 3ème cycle),<ref>Filtres digitaux autoadaptifs: algorithmes de calcul et simulation — [http://www.worldcat.org/title/filtres-digitaux-autoadaptifs-algorithmes-de-calcul-et-simulation/oclc/708539772 record] at [[WorldCat]]</ref> and Habilitation thesis ([[Thèse d'état]]),<ref>Sur l'inférence et la synthèse automatiques de fonctions LISP à partir d'exemples — [http://www.worldcat.org/title/sur-linference-et-la-synthese-automatiques-de-fonctions-lisp-a-partir-dexemples/oclc/251361381 record] at [[WorldCat]]</ref> respectively, at the [[Université de Paris VI]].<ref name="Lassez.Plotkin.1991">{{cite book | editor1=Jean-Louis Lassez | editor2=Gordon Plotkin | editor2link=Gordon Plotkin | title=Computational Logic &mdash; Essays in Honor of Alan Robinson | publisher=MIT Press | location=Cambridge/MA | isbn=978-0-262-12156-9 | year=1991 | title-link=John Alan Robinson }}</ref>{{rp|724}} In 1979, he became an associate professor at the [[Nancy University]]; 1985 he changed to the [[Université de Paris-Sud]], where he became a full professor in 1986.
He was member of the steering committee of several international computer science conferences: [[International Conference on Rewriting Techniques and Applications]] (RTA) 1989-1994, [[IEEE Symposium on Logic in Computer Science]] (LICS) 1993-1997, Conference for Computer Science Logic (CSL) 1993-1997, International Conference on Principles and Practice of Constraint Programming (CP) since 1994, and [[Federated Logic Conference]] (FLoC) 1995-1999. Since 1997, he is member of the [[EATCS]] council.<ref>[http://www.lix.polytechnique.fr/Labo/Jean-Pierre.Jouannaud/cv.html Vita]</ref>
